verbs.description: overpeer (third-person singular simple present overpeers, present participle overpeering, simple past and past participle overpeered)

examples: In Admirals’ Row  […]  Miss Sally Tregentil would overpeer her blind and draw back in a flutter lest the Major had observed her.
These patches are but meagre second growth, with here and there a gnarled birch or overpeering pine, lonely survivor of the primeval brotherhood.
